n\r\nSome residents — including a few who later died — had refused the order to evacuate for fear of losing their possessions to flames or looters, even though police guarded the streets.\r\n\r\n“I will not let go of what little I have. This represents 15 years of effort, and until I can no longer see my house, I will not leave it. My wife and my four children are in a shelter,” said Arturo Gomez.\r\n\r\nAbout 1200 people had spent a second night in one of eight such shelters set up by authorities.\r\n\r\nSome people who dared venture back after fire tore through their neighbourhoods discovered homes that had been reduced to smouldering ruins.\r\n\r\nHealth Minister Helia Molina said over and beyond reconstruction, counselling would be offered to those affected.\r\n\r\nThe blaze sparked the second mass evacuation in Valparaiso in as many weeks after the city was at the centre of a tsunami alert following a magnitude-8.2 earthquake on April 1.\r\n\r\n<ul class="ficha-prensa">\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>Nacionalidad: Australiana</li>\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>Medio: Online</li>\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>Fuente: The Australian</li>\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>Fecha: 16/04/2014</li>\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>Autor: The Australian</li>\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>Tema: Informaciones</li>\r\n<li> <span class=''none''>URL: <a href="http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/catastrophic-chile-fire-rages-for-third-day/story-e6frg6so-1226885496585" title="url" target="_blank">http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/catastrophic-chile-fire-rages-for-third-day/story-e6frg6so-1226885496585</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Catastrophic Chile fire rages for third day', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '216-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-08 20:45:52', '2014-05-08 20:45:52', '', 216, 'http://vergel439.cl/2014/05/216-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
